            <div>Team Formation Rules:<div>
                <ul>
                  <li>Each team must consist of 7 players out of which 6 would play in the match.</li>
                  <li>Team should comprise of players from a minimum of 2 different batches. (eg: BTech ‘18, MTech ‘20). Faculties and staff
                  can be considered as one batch.</li>
                  <li>If a team has any girl member then all the runs scored by the girl member would be doubled.</li>
                  <li>A team of 7 players can be formed, but only 6 players are involved in the game at any point of the match. So, while
                  batting or bowling (& fielding), any 6 of the 7 players are chosen (So, the 7th player is like a super-sub).<b>However, at least 1 girl should be among 6 players.</b></li>

                </ul>

                <br>

                <div>Game Rules:</div>
                <ul>
                  <li>Each innings would be 8 overs. </li>
                  <li>Maximum 2 players can bowl 3 overs each. It is mandatory that a girl should bowl a 1 over.</li>
                  <li>In the girl’s over the bowling team can dismiss the batsman by catching the ball on one bounce as well but in one hand.</li>
                  <li>The batting team is allowed to take a "Hallabol Over", in which runs scored by the batting team will be doubled. At the
                  same time, in this over the bowling team can dismiss the batsman by catching the ball on one bounce as well but in one
                  hand. The decision of taking the "Hallabol Over" should be made before the start of the over. It’s compulsory for every
                  team to take “Hallabol Over”. The batting team has to announce the Hallabol Over first and then the bowling may choose
                  which bowler is going to bowl that particular over.</li>
                  <li>All the usual international rules overthrow, wide, no balls are ON.</li>
                  <li>A player can be declared ‘retired hurt’ only after the completion of an over. However, retired players can bat again
                  only after every remaining player gets out.</li>
                  <li>Only throw bowling (with at max one-step run-up) will be allowed with speed restriction which will be looked after by
                  the Umpire only.</li>
                  <li>All the other rules are standard and will be announced at the time of the match.</li>
                  <li>Umpires decision would be considered final in case of any discrepancy.</li>
                </ul>
